Spicy Shrimp Soup
  --Cook's Country

2 tbsp vegetable oil
4 carrots, peeled and sliced 1/2" thick
1 onion, halved and sliced thin
2 celery ribs, sliced 1/2" thick
1 1/2 tbsp Old Bay seasoning
5 c water
8 oz red potatoes, unpeeled, cut into 3/4" pieces
6 oz linguica sausages, sliced on bias 1/2" thick
1/2 tsp pepper
1/4 tsp table salt
1 lb extra-large shrimp (21 to 25 per lb), peeled, deveined, and tails removed
3/4 c fresh or thawed frozen corn

Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add carrots, onion, and celery and cook until onion is softened, 5-7 min. Stir in Old Bay and cook until fragrant, ~15 s. Stir in water, potatoes, sausage, pepper, and salt and bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium, cover, and simmer until potatoes are tender, ~10 min. Stir in shrimp and corn. Cover and continue to cook until shrimp is cooked through, ~4 min longer. Serve.



Notes: Can sub kielbasa for the linguica
